BATON ROUGE -- - Former Catholic High, LSU star, Aaron Nola, has agreed to a four-year, $45 million extension with the Philadelphia Phillies. 
 
The deal avoids an arbitration hearing between the Nola and the club, as well as a $2 million signing bonus for the right handed ace.
 
According to ESPN's Jeff Passan, the contract includes fifth year club option of $16 million in 2023.
 
